A Process is a program that is currently being executed. It is an active entity that contains program code, data, stack, and execution state.

Simple definition:
Process = Program in execution.
Components of a Process:
Program code (text section)
Data section
Stack (function calls)
Heap (dynamic memory)
Program Counter
CPU registers
Example:

If you open a browser like Google Chrome or a text editor, each running instance is a process.
